learning_outcomes.en:
Following a successful completion of this course, students should:
Knowledge
have a systematic knowledge of the connections between human behaviour and organisation;
be familiar to the basic concepts and key areas of organisational psychology;
have the knowledge of the main principles and opportunities in applying organisational psychology.
Critical thinking
understand the impact of the organisation's internal and external environment upon the human behaviour in the organisation and have the ability to critically analyse this impact;
be able to critically analyse the principal texts and research results in organisational psychology;
be able to critically analyse problems and cases to do with human behaviour in the organisation, and provide solutions to these by drawing upon theoretical knowledge.
Presentation
be able to present comprehensive knowledge of human behaviour in the organisational setting and prove its validity in both written and oral form.
Collecting information
be able to find and make use of both written and digital information on issues relating to human behaviour in the organisation.
Approaches and attitudes
know and follow the ethical principles of operating in the context of an organization whilst performing roles in management and management consultancy;
show a desire to critically analyse organisational goals and use the knowledge in psychology to achieve these.
